## Critical Finding — Wrong Password / Credentials

Every single request is returning **401 Bad Credentials**. The credentials `v1021577:Kalyan2026$$` are **not working** against Artifactory.

The `$$` in bash is a special variable (current process ID). When you type it in the shell, bash **expands `$$` to a number** like `12345`, so the actual password being sent is `Kalyan202612345` instead of `Kalyan2026$$`.

---

## Verify This Is the Issue

```bash
# Check what $$ expands to in your shell
echo $$
# Will print something like: 23456

# This means your curl is actually sending: Kalyan202623456
echo "Kalyan2026$$"
```

---

## Fix — Quote the Password Correctly

Use **single quotes** to prevent bash expansion:

```bash
# Use single quotes around the password — prevents $$ expansion
curl -k -u 'v1021577:Kalyan2026$$' \
  "https://artifactory.jfrog.sbi/artifactory/api/storage/itepaypg-sbiepay2-php-virtual/tools/" 

# Test all three commands with single quotes:

# Test 1 — Verify credentials work
curl -k -u 'v1021577:Kalyan2026$$' \
  "https://artifactory.jfrog.sbi/artifactory/api/storage/itepaypg-sbiepay2-php-virtual/"

# Test 2 — Check local repo path
curl -k -I -u 'v1021577:Kalyan2026$$' \
  "https://artifactory.jfrog.sbi/artifactory/itepaypg-sbiepay2-php-local/tools/composer/composer.phar"

# Test 3 — Download composer.phar via virtual repo
curl -k -u 'v1021577:Kalyan2026$$' \
  "https://artifactory.jfrog.sbi/artifactory/itepaypg-sbiepay2-php-virtual/composer.phar" \
  -o /tmp/composer.phar && ls -lh /tmp/composer.phar
```

---

## Also — Use API Key Instead of Password

If your Artifactory password genuinely contains `$$` or other special characters, using an **API key** is far safer and avoids all shell escaping issues entirely.

**Generate API key:**
Artifactory UI → Top right → your username → **Edit Profile** → **Generate API Key**

Then:
```bash
# Store in a variable safely
JF_TOKEN="your-api-key-here"

curl -k -u "v1021577:${JF_TOKEN}" \
  "https://artifactory.jfrog.sbi/artifactory/api/storage/itepaypg-sbiepay2-php-virtual/"
```

And in GitLab CI variables — set `JF_TOKEN` to the API key value, which has no special characters.

---

## Summary

| Problem | Cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| All requests returning 401 | `$$` in password expands in bash double quotes | Use single quotes `'v1021577:Kalyan2026$$'` in terminal |
| CI pipeline 401 | Same or `JF_TOKEN` variable not set correctly | Use Artifactory API key — no special chars |

**Run Test 1 first with single quotes** — once that returns 200, everything else will follow.
